<item>
            <title>[CXF-3531] CXF doesn&apos;t always generate 415 when POSTing to a resource with an invalid media type</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-3531</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When you POST to a resource using an invalid Content-Type of &quot;foo&quot;, CXF doesn&apos;t return 415.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Instead, CXF throws a 500 because an IllegalArgumentException is thrown instead of a WebApplicationException.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;JDK 1.6&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12507548">CXF-3531</key>
            <summary>CXF doesn&apos;t always generate 415 when POSTing to a resource with an invalid media type</summary>
